    content: "Amazon Partnership\r\n\r\nThis one I think is going to be massive.\r\n\r\nSo we work with sellers on Amazon. We provide them a guarantee for let's say 10,000 items.\r\n\r\nPut those items on Garthbid\r\n\r\nWe then collect all the money. And then we released the Garth Amazon agent.\r\n\r\nThat agent now places orders on Amazon on behalf of all the customers. And delivers the item right to their door.\r\n\r\nSo we are now backpacking off Amazon's shipping infrastructure.\r\n\r\nThis offers Amazon sellers massive liquidity if they need and it provides Garthbid buyers with interesting events and just delivery right to their house.\r\n\r\nI don't think if this catches on Amazon will copy it. It's almost more beneficial to them that it's a separate platform. Also don't think they're going to have any problem with it whatsoever because it changes nothing about their business. We take an extra fee on top for the risk and I think it's going to be a good partnership. It also doesn't require them to sign us up or anything. We do this with the agent and I think it's all going to work out.\r\n",
